17/10/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- Greece received a non-permanent seat in the UN Security Council on Friday (15 October).
It is the second time the country has been granted a seat in the Council;
the first was in 1952.
Together with Argentina, Japan, Denmark and Tanzania, Greece will take up a non-permanent seat as of 1 January 2005 and hold it until the end of 2006.
Greek Foreign Minister Petros Molyviatis said his country would use the opportunity to work for Balkan stability and resolution of the Cyprus issue.
(ANA, Kathimerini - 16/10/04)
